18:19.280 --> 18:20.986
Give my love to Lola, will you?

18:32.572 --> 18:34.065
How was the tennis lesson?

18:34.197 --> 18:37.030
Great. The teacher says I'm a natural.

18:37.156 --> 18:39.905
He says I've got the best backside he's ever seen.

18:40.031 --> 18:41.026
That's <i>backhand</i>.

18:41.156 --> 18:42.234
Don't go in there.

18:42.364 --> 18:44.485
- Why?
- Let's talk.

18:45.698 --> 18:49.194
Okay, you're making me nervous, and I don't get nervous.

18:50.948 --> 18:52.773
Agent Lloyd just left.

18:52.906 --> 18:54.529
What's <i>he</i> doing here?

18:54.656 --> 18:56.114
He came to show me this.

19:02.282 --> 19:04.568
Damn it, Max.

19:04.699 --> 19:06.156
Is this what we're here for?

19:06.282 --> 19:08.735
No. It's not.

19:11.241 --> 19:13.278
This is not retirement at all.

19:13.407 --> 19:15.777
This is the next setup, isn't it?

19:15.908 --> 19:18.822
Babe, <i>you</i> chose this island, remember?

19:21.033 --> 19:23.522
I hope you don't think this is a gift from God.

19:23.658 --> 19:27.189
'Cause this is God messing with us.

19:32.033 --> 19:34.024
Oh, no. Max.

19:34.950 --> 19:36.609
Did Stan do this?

19:36.742 --> 19:38.484
Sort of.

19:39.576 --> 19:42.111
I figured he'd bug the place, so I started checking.

19:42.242 --> 19:44.114
Did you find any?

19:44.242 --> 19:46.447
Only what he wanted me to find.

19:47.493 --> 19:49.116
There's another one here somewhere.

19:51.576 --> 19:53.117
Now, don't worry.
I already checked.

19:53.243 --> 19:54.404
There's nothing in there.

19:54.535 --> 19:55.992
That's the problem.

19:56.118 --> 19:57.694
There's nothing in here.

20:02.410 --> 20:03.903
What is it?
What's wrong?

20:04.035 --> 20:06.571
I hid the bullet in the camera.

20:06.702 --> 20:08.278
What bullet?

20:08.410 --> 20:10.567
The one he shot you with.

20:10.702 --> 20:12.195
Oh, no.

20:13.452 --> 20:16.783
I kept it to remind me of how close I came to losing you.

20:16.911 --> 20:19.364
Lola, you know that bullet puts me on the scene.

20:19.494 --> 20:22.161
I know, I know. I'm sorry.

20:22.286 --> 20:24.241
I'll get it back.

20:39.912 --> 20:42.483
Good morning, Mr. Lloyd. Your suite is ready.

20:42.621 --> 20:44.860
- Suite?
- Suite, sir.

20:44.996 --> 20:46.868
It's a larger room.

20:48.329 --> 20:52.572
Atlantis reserves this bridge suite for our more dignified guests.

20:55.871 --> 20:58.953
Breakfast is on the house, these are vouchers for free tennis lessons,

20:59.080 --> 21:02.944
complimentary skin exfoliant, seaweed body wrap and facial scrub,

21:03.080 --> 21:05.651
located in the spa on the club level.

21:05.788 --> 21:07.162
Also, please remember.

21:07.289 --> 21:12.029
Shoes and shirt are required in all public spaces at all times.

21:43.999 --> 21:45.160
State your business.

21:45.291 --> 21:48.289
You can't bribe me with a seaweed body wrap, Max.

21:48.416 --> 21:49.992
This doesn't buy you one bit of space.

21:50.124 --> 21:52.162
I'm gonna be on you wherever you go.

21:52.291 --> 21:53.369
It's no bribe, Stanley.

21:53.499 --> 21:55.822
I just want you to see that if you lead the kind of life I do,

21:55.958 --> 21:58.079
stealing is the last thing on your mind.

22:00.541 --> 22:01.999
Mr. Lloyd.

22:02.125 --> 22:04.116
Are you ready for your massage?

22:05.500 --> 22:07.290
I'll do your back.

22:07.417 --> 22:09.242
I'll do your front.

22:10.500 --> 22:11.910
You son of a bitch.

22:21.918 --> 22:23.576
- Lola?
- Yeah.

22:25.126 --> 22:28.124
- He hid it in a black jewelry box.
- Good job.

22:28.251 --> 22:29.495
Thank you.

22:29.626 --> 22:31.451
Talented masseuse.

22:32.335 --> 22:33.448
You get rid of it this time.

22:33.585 --> 22:35.042
I will.

22:35.918 --> 22:37.790
Good evening.
May I take your order?

22:39.835 --> 22:40.532
No, thank you.

22:40.559 --> 22:41.852
I just lost my appetite.

22:41.960 --> 22:43.122
Just as well.

22:43.252 --> 22:46.001
I don't take orders from criminals, I arrest them.

22:46.127 --> 22:47.620
Or fall asleep trying.

22:48.252 --> 22:49.875
So you're admitting you were there.

22:50.002 --> 22:52.917
No. I read about it in the papers, just like everyone else.

22:53.044 --> 22:54.952
You're famous.

22:55.919 --> 22:57.329
I'm a punchline.

22:58.003 --> 23:02.079
But like my grandma used to say, he who laughs last laughs loudest.

23:02.211 --> 23:03.918
By the way, return that movie, would you?

23:04.045 --> 23:05.585
The store called.

23:05.712 --> 23:07.370
I haven't finished it yet.

23:07.503 --> 23:10.585
They catch the thief, but it's not who you think it is.

23:10.712 --> 23:12.619
I don't like those twist endings.

23:12.754 --> 23:14.128
Well, we don't like you.

23:14.254 --> 23:16.956
- Aw.
- Lola.

23:18.629 --> 23:20.122
They're playing your song.

23:20.254 --> 23:23.169
Why don't you take Stanley for a dance?

23:23.296 --> 23:24.836
He's feeling lonely.

23:24.963 --> 23:27.533
And I am feeling charitable.

23:28.379 --> 23:29.872
Let's go, Stan.

23:30.004 --> 23:31.083
Really?

23:32.671 --> 23:34.709
I'll try to have her back by dawn.

23:49.297 --> 23:50.459
Constable...

23:52.422 --> 23:53.702
Can I help you?

23:53.839 --> 23:55.629
I wanna talk to Mooré.

23:55.756 --> 23:57.000
Get out of the way.

23:57.131 --> 23:59.915
Monsieur Mooré is currently socializing.

24:00.048 --> 24:02.916
Interrupting a man's leisure is harassment.

24:03.048 --> 24:05.334
That's not harassment.

24:06.756 --> 24:08.000
You feel that?

24:08.131 --> 24:10.336
- Ooh.
- That's harassment.

24:10.465 --> 24:14.541
And you tell your boss this is just the beginning.

24:14.674 --> 24:17.921
I have two hands, and I can't be bought.

24:18.049 --> 24:19.044
Ooh.

24:23.007 --> 24:24.142
Excuse me, constable.

24:24.169 --> 24:25.736
May I have a word with you?

24:34.550 --> 24:38.129
<i>Audrey, where you get that sugar?</i>

24:38.258 --> 24:40.296
Listen, Stan, I know what you're doing.

24:40.425 --> 24:44.419
But if you drag Max into your game, he will not lose.

24:44.550 --> 24:46.541
Eventually, they all lose.

24:46.675 --> 24:48.216
Not my Max.

24:48.342 --> 24:50.712
Do yourself a favor--
leave us alone.

24:50.842 --> 24:54.753
We're just a couple of retirees trying to enjoy the island life.

24:54.884 --> 24:58.297
All the same, I'll stick around, see what develops.

24:59.843 --> 25:01.004
Excuse me.

25:01.134 --> 25:01.835
In a second, honey.

25:01.862 --> 25:02.783
You'll get your chance.

25:02.884 --> 25:05.634
Damn, I got the stink on me tonight.

25:05.760 --> 25:07.418
Step off the dance floor, sir.

25:08.260 --> 25:09.669
Hey!

25:09.801 --> 25:11.460
- Have fun, Stan.
- Hey. Lola!

25:11.593 --> 25:14.129
Police.
Raise your hands, sir.

25:15.260 --> 25:17.879
I'm law.
Federal B.I.?

25:24.677 --> 25:28.801
It is illegal on this island to carry a concealed weapon without a permit.

25:28.927 --> 25:30.550
I'm working a suspect.

25:33.636 --> 25:36.303
Are you not supposed to inform local authorities when you arrive,

25:36.428 --> 25:38.881
Agent Stanley P. Lloyd?

25:42.220 --> 25:44.341
- You know him?
- He's my suspect.

25:44.470 --> 25:47.503
Well, we're still gonna have to take this to the station and register it.

25:47.637 --> 25:48.964
You're letting the criminal go.

25:49.095 --> 25:50.257
This is crazy.

25:50.387 --> 25:51.880
You think this is crazy?

25:52.012 --> 25:54.761
Your dancing, <i>that</i> was crazy.

25:54.887 --> 25:56.380
This way, Agent Lloyd.

25:56.512 --> 25:58.420
Welcome to paradise.

26:03.429 --> 26:04.673
Okay.

26:04.804 --> 26:07.672
- The watermarks and holograms match.
- Oh.

26:07.805 --> 26:09.842
But I still have to register the gun.

26:15.638 --> 26:17.179
You have a nice smile.

26:17.305 --> 26:19.047
I haven't smiled at you.

26:19.180 --> 26:20.721
You will.

26:23.305 --> 26:25.711
That's just the way I feel about it, and they have to deal with it.

26:25.847 --> 26:26.961
Yes, sir.

26:27.097 --> 26:28.922
Ah, Sophie.

26:29.056 --> 26:30.845
I need to speak to you.

26:30.972 --> 26:33.508
I'm getting complaints about you bothering Henri Mooré.

26:33.639 --> 26:35.547
Just doing my job, Zacharias.

26:35.681 --> 26:37.672
The man is practically the unofficial mayor of the island.

26:37.806 --> 26:39.382
In one year, he's made everyone here like him,

26:39.515 --> 26:41.304
something you haven't been able to do in a lifetime.

26:41.431 --> 26:44.134
I guess we can't all be the kiss-ass politician you are.

26:44.973 --> 26:47.841
I want you to stay behind tonight so we can discuss your attitude.

26:47.973 --> 26:49.549
You knew about my attitude the day we got married

26:49.682 --> 26:51.139
and knew about it the day we got divorced.

26:51.265 --> 26:54.014
You're not gonna learn any more about it tonight.

26:54.140 --> 26:58.004
Besides, I have plans with Special Agent Lloyd of the FBI.

26:58.141 --> 27:00.131
He's just arrived on the island.

27:00.849 --> 27:01.963
Is that so?

27:02.891 --> 27:03.886
Shall we?

27:04.016 --> 27:05.592
We shall.

27:10.433 --> 27:12.091
She's feisty.

27:17.267 --> 27:20.679
Mmm. Isn't it beautiful?

27:22.100 --> 27:23.214
Yeah.

27:25.434 --> 27:27.140
Is it enough?

27:27.934 --> 27:29.095
Of course it is.

27:42.018 --> 27:45.300
Some people say the only way to rid yourself of temptation

27:45.435 --> 27:47.509
is to yield to it.

27:49.727 --> 27:51.385
I don't know about that.

27:53.518 --> 27:58.472
I say turn your back on temptation...

27:59.310 --> 28:04.513
...or substitute something more tempting.

28:18.811 --> 28:21.098
See how easy that was?

28:30.354 --> 28:32.724
What's the shortest amount of time you've ever known a guy

28:32.854 --> 28:36.302
before you kissed him?

28:36.979 --> 28:39.728
I see what you're thinking, and you can forget it.

28:39.854 --> 28:43.683
Guys come down to this island looking for a slice of paradise with a local girl,

28:43.813 --> 28:46.053
and they will say anything to get it.

28:47.230 --> 28:49.801
I resent being lumped in with all guys,

28:49.938 --> 28:53.102
though, admittedly, I would say anything right now.

28:53.230 --> 28:55.434
How long have you been chasing Max?

28:57.522 --> 29:01.432
Seven years-- ever since the first Napoleon Diamond went missing.

29:01.564 --> 29:04.562
I got to the scene, took a few shots at the getaway car.

29:04.689 --> 29:09.311
Next day, bottle of champagne arrives at FBI Headquarters for me,

29:09.439 --> 29:14.144
with a note says, "Aim for the tires next time."

29:14.273 --> 29:15.896
He was baiting you.

29:16.023 --> 29:18.891
- Hmm.
- Is there a money trail?

29:19.023 --> 29:21.974
Everything's plain-- taxes, bank accounts.

29:22.107 --> 29:25.270
He doesn't buy expensive paintings, yachts, nothing.

29:25.398 --> 29:30.388
I think it's more about the challenge and the alibi-- that's his work of art.

29:30.524 --> 29:32.265
Sounds like you admire him.

29:33.315 --> 29:36.847
Would I like to live one day in his velvety slippers?

29:36.982 --> 29:38.356
Maybe.

29:38.482 --> 29:40.307
But I don't admire him.

29:40.441 --> 29:42.396
He's beat me too many times for that.

29:42.524 --> 29:44.645
Maybe you need the female touch.

29:46.274 --> 29:48.230
That's exactly what I need.

29:48.358 --> 29:51.806
Listen, I want a big arrest, you need local help.

29:51.941 --> 29:54.228
I'll extend the FBI courtesy on this one.

29:54.358 --> 29:56.645
As long as I'm riding shotgun.

30:04.442 --> 30:05.604
What's going on?

30:05.734 --> 30:07.771
I'm expanding the deck.

30:07.901 --> 30:09.477
You're trying to stay busy.

30:09.609 --> 30:12.726
Look, on this deck, we are going to sit here

30:12.859 --> 30:15.774
and watch sunsets until we get old.

30:16.609 --> 30:18.150
Can't wait.

30:18.276 --> 30:19.686
Where are you going?

30:19.818 --> 30:21.441
You said I need a hobby.

30:21.568 --> 30:23.475
I guess I'll go find one.

30:23.610 --> 30:24.605
Really?

30:24.735 --> 30:26.726
I'll call you later.

