01:00:02.121 --> 01:00:03.116
Hello.

01:00:03.246 --> 01:00:05.036
Mr. Burdett, it's Luc from the bar.

01:00:05.163 --> 01:00:08.244
There's a guest down here that's bombed that's shouting your name.

01:00:08.371 --> 01:00:11.156
Welcome to paradise, Frank!

01:00:13.163 --> 01:00:18.864
Well, it's only paradise for criminals, like Max Burdett.

01:00:18.997 --> 01:00:22.742
Yeah. I hear him.
I'll be right there.

01:00:26.456 --> 01:00:27.865
- Where'd he go?
- Over there.

01:00:27.997 --> 01:00:29.241
Oh, thanks, Luc.

01:00:32.331 --> 01:00:33.954
What are you doing to yourself?
What's wrong?

01:00:34.081 --> 01:00:35.111
- Nothing.
- Nothing's wrong?

01:00:37.123 --> 01:00:39.327
Me and Sophie hooked up.

01:00:39.456 --> 01:00:41.198
And it was beautiful.

01:00:42.331 --> 01:00:44.121
But it's only gonna last for one more day.

01:00:44.248 --> 01:00:45.492
Why is that?

01:00:45.623 --> 01:00:48.242
Because the ship's only gonna be here 24 more hours,

01:00:48.373 --> 01:00:49.996
and you're gonna clip Napoleon Ill

01:00:50.124 --> 01:00:51.996
and make me look like a jerk again.

01:00:55.832 --> 01:00:57.740
- I'll have another one!
- You've had enough.

01:00:57.874 --> 01:00:59.664
You are not my daddy.

01:00:59.791 --> 01:01:03.121
I didn't take you as an umbrella kind of guy, Stan.

01:01:03.249 --> 01:01:05.157
These remoras really have a kick to 'em.

01:01:05.291 --> 01:01:06.235
Hey, Stan, buck up.

01:01:06.262 --> 01:01:07.355
You're a good agent.

01:01:07.458 --> 01:01:09.413
No, I'm not.

01:01:09.541 --> 01:01:12.409
You know, I used to blame you, but now I see it clearly.

01:01:12.541 --> 01:01:14.911
It's not you, it's me.

01:01:15.042 --> 01:01:16.914
You've got genius, man.

01:01:17.042 --> 01:01:21.367
If I had an ounce of what you have, I'd never stop.

01:01:21.500 --> 01:01:25.162
You've got a gift, man.
It's inspiring.

01:01:27.126 --> 01:01:29.246
I love these remoras!

01:01:29.376 --> 01:01:32.243
Bartender! Give me another one!

01:01:39.793 --> 01:01:41.583
It's okay, Stan.
It's okay.

01:01:41.710 --> 01:01:43.967
Luc, you're not working tonight, right?

01:01:43.994 --> 01:01:45.267
Give us a hand here.

01:01:45.376 --> 01:01:47.083
Come on, Stan, here you go.
Come on.

01:01:47.210 --> 01:01:49.165
Here you go, buddy.
Yeah.

01:01:50.627 --> 01:01:52.084
Come on, come on.

01:01:52.919 --> 01:01:54.826
What about me?!

01:01:56.210 --> 01:01:58.082
That's it, Stanley.

01:01:58.211 --> 01:01:59.787
Here you go.

01:01:59.919 --> 01:02:01.080
That's it.

01:02:03.169 --> 01:02:04.745
That's it. Here we go.

01:02:18.295 --> 01:02:20.665
You tell anyone I tucked him in,
I'll kill you.

01:02:21.462 --> 01:02:24.211
- Sure thing, Mr. Burdett.
- Call me Max.

01:02:24.379 --> 01:02:26.120
- Max.
- Okay.

01:02:53.838 --> 01:02:54.917
Lola!

01:02:55.130 --> 01:02:57.619
It's locked.
And don't try to break in.

01:02:57.839 --> 01:02:58.869
You're not welcome.

01:03:01.297 --> 01:03:02.873
I finished the deck.

01:03:03.006 --> 01:03:06.336
You promised to spend the first sunset on it together.

01:03:06.464 --> 01:03:08.620
- Lola.
- That's not all.

01:03:09.589 --> 01:03:11.047
I found your notebook.

01:03:12.048 --> 01:03:14.085
Lola.

01:03:14.215 --> 01:03:16.668
I'll sit down right now and write my vows, okay?

01:03:21.507 --> 01:03:24.505
The vows are not for me, they're for you.

01:03:24.632 --> 01:03:27.713
You have to figure out if what we have means anything to you.

01:03:30.965 --> 01:03:32.044
Come on, Max.

01:03:32.882 --> 01:03:34.920
Do you really think the third one's gonna make you whole?

01:03:38.299 --> 01:03:41.416
- I don't know.
- Well, don't come back until you do.

01:03:43.299 --> 01:03:45.171
Where am I supposed to go?

01:03:49.925 --> 01:03:51.003
She threw me out.

01:03:52.508 --> 01:03:54.298
Why is it my problem?

01:03:54.425 --> 01:03:56.795
'Cause every hotel on the island is booked.

01:04:02.259 --> 01:04:04.582
Can I move this surveillance stuff?

01:04:04.717 --> 01:04:06.162
Don't mess with it!

01:04:06.189 --> 01:04:07.860
It's very expensive.

01:04:08.717 --> 01:04:12.415
Listen, I'm not gonna sleep on the floor.

01:04:12.551 --> 01:04:15.336
Well, I guess you're out of luck.

01:04:15.468 --> 01:04:16.747
We both are.

01:04:17.885 --> 01:04:19.046
Move over.

01:04:24.760 --> 01:04:25.755
Shit.

01:04:36.469 --> 01:04:37.796
So what'd you do?

01:04:39.136 --> 01:04:42.502
I missed our first sunset on her new deck.

01:04:43.886 --> 01:04:44.881
That's it?

01:04:53.011 --> 01:04:54.967
I'm no good at sunsets.

01:04:57.137 --> 01:04:58.629
Of course you're not.

01:04:59.553 --> 01:05:03.049
The world is divided up between people who like to watch the sunset

01:05:03.220 --> 01:05:04.464
and those who don't.

01:05:05.220 --> 01:05:06.500
Yeah.

01:05:06.637 --> 01:05:09.470
People like you are never happy.

01:05:09.596 --> 01:05:14.419
You're anxious, type-A, egocentric perfectionists who can't sit still

01:05:14.554 --> 01:05:18.418
and die alone with a million bucks and a thousand regrets.

01:05:19.430 --> 01:05:22.096
The people who can relax, enjoy the sunset,

01:05:22.221 --> 01:05:26.381
hold hands at the end of the day--
they're the happy ones.

01:05:30.305 --> 01:05:32.047
So why can't you do that?

01:05:36.097 --> 01:05:37.424
Because of you.

01:05:42.431 --> 01:05:44.089
Don't hog the blanket.

01:05:49.348 --> 01:05:51.137
- Good night, Max.
- Good night.

01:06:37.434 --> 01:06:39.471
You know, the Bureau's got a "don't ask, don't tell" policy,

01:06:39.600 --> 01:06:41.472
but this is pushing it, Stan.

01:06:41.601 --> 01:06:43.887
Kowalski, Stafford.

01:06:44.017 --> 01:06:45.012
Sophie?

01:06:45.226 --> 01:06:47.761
The L.A. office got a call from Inspector Bethel here.

01:06:47.893 --> 01:06:51.140
He wanted to know the scope of the FBI's operation on the island.

01:06:51.268 --> 01:06:53.342
Since we don't have an operation on the island,

01:06:53.476 --> 01:06:55.218
we felt we'd come here and check it out.

01:06:55.351 --> 01:06:56.678
What's he talking about, Stan?

01:06:56.810 --> 01:06:58.007
Let me explain.

01:06:58.143 --> 01:06:59.075
He's on suspension.

01:06:59.103 --> 01:07:00.622
He has been for three months.

01:07:00.727 --> 01:07:01.805
Suspension?

01:07:01.935 --> 01:07:04.424
He was deemed unstable after he lost Napoleon II.

01:07:04.560 --> 01:07:06.017
You told me you were here on the case.

01:07:06.144 --> 01:07:07.601
I am here on the case,

01:07:07.727 --> 01:07:11.342
and once I bust this guy, get reinstated, upped,

01:07:11.477 --> 01:07:12.851
these slobs will be saluting me.

01:07:12.977 --> 01:07:14.256
Are you guys dating?

01:07:14.394 --> 01:07:16.219
He's nothing but a suspect to me.

01:07:16.352 --> 01:07:18.888
- Oh, really?
- That's not what these show.

01:07:19.561 --> 01:07:21.219
Your suspect's paying for this suite.

01:07:21.353 --> 01:07:22.845
And the seaweed body wraps.

01:07:22.978 --> 01:07:24.636
You two look pretty chummy.

01:07:27.353 --> 01:07:29.676
So you lied to me, Stan.

01:07:29.811 --> 01:07:32.514
And you got your slice of paradise, hmm?

01:07:33.228 --> 01:07:35.266
I hope it was everything you thought it would be.

01:07:35.395 --> 01:07:36.592
Sophie...

01:07:36.728 --> 01:07:39.929
You might want to do more of a background check next time

01:07:40.062 --> 01:07:41.519
before you partner up.

01:07:46.646 --> 01:07:49.430
She didn't have to be so hard on you, you know?

01:07:49.563 --> 01:07:51.139
Storming out like that.

01:07:51.271 --> 01:07:53.096
She's got grounds.

01:07:53.229 --> 01:07:56.263
The thing you gotta understand about us law enforcement types

01:07:56.396 --> 01:07:58.553
is we don't much appreciate lying.

01:07:58.688 --> 01:08:01.639
Come on, Stan, you fibbed, maybe withheld a little.

01:08:01.771 --> 01:08:03.181
But lie? Nah.

01:08:04.647 --> 01:08:08.475
You are an FBI agent working a case.

01:08:09.564 --> 01:08:11.601
You know, when you put it like that, it doesn't sound so bad.

01:08:11.730 --> 01:08:13.520
I could explain it to her.

01:08:14.772 --> 01:08:16.099
What about you?

01:08:16.231 --> 01:08:18.600
You are a hell of a catch.

01:08:18.731 --> 01:08:21.100
I've seen the way you are with Lola.

01:08:21.231 --> 01:08:22.392
You love that girl.

01:08:22.523 --> 01:08:25.058
So you're working out some personal issues.

01:08:25.189 --> 01:08:27.145
All you need is a little support.

01:08:27.273 --> 01:08:28.350
Exactly.

01:08:28.481 --> 01:08:30.768
Hell, I could make her understand.

01:08:37.689 --> 01:08:40.688
Max can't eat, can't sleep.

01:08:40.814 --> 01:08:42.723
He's like an injured bird.

01:08:42.857 --> 01:08:45.096
Stan's hurt.
He's in pain.

01:08:45.232 --> 01:08:46.938
He's like a wounded dog.

01:08:47.066 --> 01:08:48.216
He needs you, Lola.

01:08:48.243 --> 01:08:49.758
You're his better half.

01:08:49.857 --> 01:08:51.100
Just give him one more chance.

01:08:51.232 --> 01:08:53.104
He's a good guy, Sophie.

01:08:53.233 --> 01:08:56.515
I'm sure he's a liar, but that comes with the job.

01:08:57.566 --> 01:08:58.450
I don't know.

01:08:58.477 --> 01:09:00.377
This is all a bit strange.

01:09:00.483 --> 01:09:02.189
What do you think, Lola?

01:09:02.316 --> 01:09:03.662
I don't buy a word of it.

01:09:03.689 --> 01:09:04.712
I'm with you.

01:09:04.899 --> 01:09:06.144
- No, no, no.
- Hey, hey, hey.

01:09:06.274 --> 01:09:06.779
Listen, hear us out.

01:09:06.807 --> 01:09:07.462
Come on, one second.

01:09:07.567 --> 01:09:08.562
Look...

01:09:10.733 --> 01:09:13.304
Tonight the lies stop.

01:09:13.442 --> 01:09:14.899
He's serious. It's over.

01:09:15.024 --> 01:09:17.644
He's not chasin' it, and I'm not chasin' him.

01:09:17.776 --> 01:09:21.224
I'm sorry, but I won't believe you until that ship is gone.

01:09:21.359 --> 01:09:23.397
And we still got a few hours before she sails.

01:09:23.526 --> 01:09:25.647
Look, I can't make that ship disappear tonight,

01:09:25.776 --> 01:09:27.020
but I can make us disappear.

01:09:27.151 --> 01:09:28.987
What are you talking about?

01:09:29.014 --> 01:09:30.506
I found a hobby.

01:09:32.484 --> 01:09:33.015
Wait a minute.

01:09:33.042 --> 01:09:34.252
You didn't tell me about this.

01:09:34.359 --> 01:09:36.149
When we come up for air,

01:09:36.277 --> 01:09:40.057
that ship will be headed to Paris and the diamond will be gone forever.

01:10:02.611 --> 01:10:04.436
So, where you taking us?

01:10:04.570 --> 01:10:06.726
We're headed to a hidden reef where there's rumored to be

01:10:06.861 --> 01:10:09.231
100 million in gold somewhere among the wreckage.

01:10:10.195 --> 01:10:11.392
You're kidding.

01:10:14.737 --> 01:10:15.732
Wow!

01:10:15.862 --> 01:10:17.568
Look at this.

01:10:17.695 --> 01:10:20.729
Yeah, these ships have been down here since the '40s,

01:10:20.862 --> 01:10:23.149
but nobody's ever found any gold.

01:10:23.279 --> 01:10:26.111
Well, maybe with the help of the FBI we'll get lucky.

01:10:27.279 --> 01:10:29.069
My money's on Max.

01:10:29.196 --> 01:10:33.107
100 million four ways-- that's 25 million apiece if we split it.

01:10:37.530 --> 01:10:39.816
Have any idea where to start?

01:10:39.947 --> 01:10:41.783
It could be anywhere down here.

01:10:41.810 --> 01:10:43.587
Let's split up, look around.

01:10:45.405 --> 01:10:47.488
You guys sure this is safe?

01:10:47.515 --> 01:10:49.674
I'm allergic to shellfish.

01:10:49.780 --> 01:10:51.570
You've got nothing to worry about.

01:10:51.597 --> 01:10:53.386
I've seen how you handle sharks.

01:11:21.740 --> 01:11:25.236
When we get back, I'm buying everyone umbrella drinks.

01:11:32.241 --> 01:11:35.986
Hey, little guy, have you seen any gold down here?

01:11:43.700 --> 01:11:47.315
Hey, Max, I'm counting on you to make me a rich man.

01:12:28.744 --> 01:12:31.411
Lola, hypothetically speaking,

01:12:31.536 --> 01:12:34.285
what's it like to hold 25 million in your hands?

01:12:35.203 --> 01:12:37.489
I have no idea what you're talking about.

01:12:38.328 --> 01:12:39.323
Right.

01:12:54.204 --> 01:12:56.953
- Good night, old-timer.
- Eat shit.

01:13:36.414 --> 01:13:38.073
What the hell is that?

01:13:41.248 --> 01:13:43.819
There is an intruder in Storage Facility B.

01:13:43.956 --> 01:13:45.273
- <i>Attempted break-in in progress.</i>

01:13:45.300 --> 01:13:46.056
- Son of a bitch!

01:13:46.165 --> 01:13:48.535
<i>All security to Storage Facility B.</i>

01:15:12.086 --> 01:15:13.081
<i>Hey, Max.</i>

01:15:16.003 --> 01:15:16.998
What's up?

01:15:17.128 --> 01:15:19.000
Where are you?

01:15:19.128 --> 01:15:21.533
Oh, I'm somewhere inside the ship.

01:15:21.670 --> 01:15:24.917
Oh, yeah, me too.
Thanks, that helps a lot.

01:15:25.045 --> 01:15:28.292
Max, did you say you were <i>inside</i> the ship?

01:15:29.129 --> 01:15:31.534
Yeah, it's amazing.

01:15:31.670 --> 01:15:34.834
Hmm. Really?
What do you see?

01:15:34.962 --> 01:15:36.089
<i>It's pretty dark.</i>

01:15:36.116 --> 01:15:38.769
<i>I think I'm in the captain's quarters.</i>

01:15:38.879 --> 01:15:40.455
That's interesting.

01:15:46.171 --> 01:15:50.117
Max, suddenly I don't feel like having an umbrella drink.

01:16:02.380 --> 01:16:04.999
I'm beginning to think we're gonna go home empty-handed.

01:16:05.131 --> 01:16:05.918
Where are you, Max?

01:16:05.945 --> 01:16:07.562
I'm gonna come hunt with you a while.

01:16:07.672 --> 01:16:09.877
I'm coming to you.

01:16:10.714 --> 01:16:11.894
How you see me?

01:16:11.922 --> 01:16:13.573
I cut the red wire.

01:16:13.673 --> 01:16:15.193
Ah, nice work, genius.

01:16:15.220 --> 01:16:17.775
You cut the heating to the Jacuzzi.

01:16:20.173 --> 01:16:22.626
<i>Max, you at the stern?</i>

01:16:24.923 --> 01:16:26.120
<i>Max?</i>

01:16:29.590 --> 01:16:32.126
<i>Stan Lloyd to Max Burdett.</i>
<i>Come in.</i>

01:16:36.091 --> 01:16:38.579
Who'd he think he was, the Invisible Man?

01:16:41.674 --> 01:16:42.918
Dear God.

01:16:43.049 --> 01:16:45.123
Shit.

01:16:45.258 --> 01:16:46.118
It was a diversion.

01:16:46.145 --> 01:16:47.321
Get back to the diamond!

01:16:49.341 --> 01:16:51.249
<i>Max, where are you?</i>

01:16:58.508 --> 01:16:59.966
<i>Will you answer me?</i>

01:17:00.092 --> 01:17:01.336
<i>Hello!</i>

01:17:01.467 --> 01:17:02.664
There!

01:17:10.301 --> 01:17:11.433
He's in the vents!

01:17:11.460 --> 01:17:12.780
He got the diamond!

01:17:12.884 --> 01:17:14.507
Max, what was that?

01:17:14.634 --> 01:17:16.257
<i>Max!</i>

01:17:16.384 --> 01:17:18.174
I think he left his radio.

01:17:18.301 --> 01:17:20.588
I thought I heard something else.

01:17:21.301 --> 01:17:22.254
<i>Where'd you go?</i>

01:17:22.282 --> 01:17:23.614
<i>Is something wrong?</i>

01:17:39.927 --> 01:17:41.799
Nice costume.

01:17:43.177 --> 01:17:44.670
- Thanks.
- You're welcome.

01:17:46.386 --> 01:17:48.875
<i>Party all the time, party all the time</i>

01:17:49.011 --> 01:17:51.416
<i>Party all the time</i>

01:17:51.553 --> 01:17:54.586
<i>My girl wants to party all the time...</i>

01:17:54.720 --> 01:17:57.125
Go back to your cabin, please.

01:17:58.553 --> 01:18:00.509
Aha, there you are!

01:18:00.720 --> 01:18:01.834
Hey, Max, come on.

01:18:02.053 --> 01:18:03.128
Last night we were spooning.

01:18:03.156 --> 01:18:04.154
Now you're running away?

01:18:05.512 --> 01:18:06.921
<i>Come on!</i>

01:18:07.595 --> 01:18:09.800
Yoo-hoo, Max.

01:18:26.638 --> 01:18:29.553
Oh, I get it.
A little hide-and-seek.

01:18:38.847 --> 01:18:41.881
Like I told you on the boat, I caught 'em all.

01:18:49.431 --> 01:18:52.050
You're good, but you're not that good.

01:18:57.681 --> 01:19:01.592
You know what they say--
the FBI always gets their man.

01:19:05.098 --> 01:19:06.591
Max!

01:19:06.724 --> 01:19:08.300
I'm having an air problem!

01:19:09.474 --> 01:19:11.215
Stan, are you okay?

01:19:11.349 --> 01:19:14.098
I can't breathe! Help!

01:19:16.224 --> 01:19:17.551
Where are you, Stan?

01:19:20.558 --> 01:19:22.134
I'm coming, Stan.

01:19:22.266 --> 01:19:25.015
It's okay, Stan.
I'm right here.

01:19:25.141 --> 01:19:26.303
Take off your mask.

01:19:27.266 --> 01:19:28.344
I got him, honey.

01:19:28.475 --> 01:19:29.967
I'm right here.

01:19:31.100 --> 01:19:32.889
You're okay, Stan.

01:19:35.267 --> 01:19:37.222
Nothing to worry about, partner.

01:19:42.934 --> 01:19:45.636
I saw my life flash before my eyes.

01:19:45.851 --> 01:19:48.090
Leave it to me to get the faulty regulator.

01:19:48.267 --> 01:19:50.637
You know, I never dove before.

01:19:51.309 --> 01:19:52.875
I would like to propose a toast.

01:19:52.902 --> 01:19:54.369
What are we celebrating?

01:19:55.226 --> 01:19:56.221
Retirement.

01:19:57.935 --> 01:19:59.475
- I'll drink to that.
- Good.

01:20:03.685 --> 01:20:04.680
Hello.

01:20:06.518 --> 01:20:07.762
What?

01:20:07.893 --> 01:20:09.090
How?

